    dc:title "A new genus for “ Neocallichirus ” grandis Karasawa & Goda, 1996, a ghost shrimp species (Decapoda: Axiidea: Callianassidae) heretofore known only by fossil materials" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2852489>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2852491>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2852501>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2852497>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2852507>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2852515> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2852489>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Laticallichirus grandis (Karasawa & Goda, 1996) n. comb., male (18.2 mm), CBM-ZC 15247. A, carapace and cephalic appendages, dorsal view; B, thoracic shield on thoracomere 7 (between coxae of pereopods 4); C, pleomeres 1 and 2, dorsal view; D, pleomeres 3–5; E, pleomere 6 and telson, dorsal view; F, telson, dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2852489/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2852491>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Laticallichirus grandis (Karasawa & Goda, 1996) n. comb., male (18.2 mm), CBM-ZC 15247. A, carapace and left thoracic appendages, lateral view; B, anterior part of carapace and cephalic appendages, dorsal view (setae partially omitted); C, left pleopod 1, posterior view; D, left pleopod 2, anterior view; E, same, posterior view (setae omitted); F, distal part of endopod of left pleopod 2, anterior view; G, left pleopod 3, anterior view (setae omitted); H, same, posterior view; I, detail of appendix interna of left pleopod 3." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2852491/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2852501>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Laticallichirus grandis (Karasawa & Goda, 1996) n. comb.. A, B, D, E, H–J, male (18.2 mm), CBM-ZC 15247; C, F, G, female (cl 16.1 mm), CBM-ZC 15249. A, left maxilliped 3, outer view; B, same, inner view (setae partially omitted); C, left pereopod 2, outer view; D, right pereopod 3, outer view; E, same, carpus to dactylus, inner view (setae omitted); F, right pereopod 4, outer view; G, same, propodus and dactylus, inner view (setae omitted); H, same, details of fixed finger of propodus, outer view; I, left pereopod 5, outer view; J, same, chela, inner view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2852501/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2852497>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Laticallichirus grandis (Karasawa & Goda, 1996) n. comb., male (18.2 mm), CBM-ZC 15247. A, left major cheliped, outer view; B, same, merus to chela, inner view (setae partially omitted); C, chela, upper view (setae omitted); D, right minor cheliped, outer view; E, same, merus to chela, inner view (setae partially omitted)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2852497/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2852507>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Laticallichirus grandis (Karasawa & Goda, 1996) n. comb., female (cl 16.1 mm), CBM-ZC 15249. A, left major cheliped, outer view; B, same, carpus, inner view; C, left pleopod 1, posterior view; D, same, distal article, different view; E, left pleopod 2, posterior view; F, same, details of distal part of endopod, posterior view (setae omitted)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2852507/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2852515>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Maximum likelihood phylogeny among species of Callichirinae based on 429 bp of 16S rRNA gene; node values represent bootstrap values (1000 replicates). GenBank/EMBL/DDBJ accession numbers are indicated for each species. The tree with the highest log likelihood (-4580.23) is shown." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2852515/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

